<doc id="523576" wikidata="Q4758441" url="?curid=523576" title="Andrew Rowe">
<text>Andrew John Bernard Rowe (11 September 1935 – 21 November 2008) was a politician in the United Kingdom. He was born in London. He served as Conservative Party Member of Parliament for Mid Kent from 1983 to 1997 and its successor constituency Faversham and Mid Kent from 1997 until he stepped down in 2001. He was replaced by Hugh Robertson.

He was educated at Eton College and Merton College, Oxford (MA).

He was the father of actor Nicholas Rowe. He was also the founding Father of the UK Youth Parliament.

