==Discography==

* &quot;Bangkok Shocks, Saigon Shakes, Hanoi Rocks&quot; (1981)
* &quot;Oriental Beat&quot; (1982)
* &quot;Self Destruction Blues&quot; (1982)
* &quot;Back to Mystery City&quot; (1983)
* &quot;Two Steps from the Move&quot; (1984)
* &quot;Twelve Shots on the Rocks&quot; (2002)
* &quot;Another Hostile Takeover&quot; (2005)
* &quot;Street Poetry&quot; (2007)

==Videography==
*&quot;All Those Wasted Years&quot; – The Marquee Club
*&quot;The Nottingham Tapes&quot; – Rock City (in Nottingham)
*&quot;Buried Alive&quot; – Last show at the Tavastia Club

==Tours==

* Bangkok Shocks, Saigon Shakes - (1981)
* Oriental Beat - (1982)
* Self Destruction Blues - (1982)
* Back To Mystery City - (1983)
* Two Steps From The Move - (1984)
;including cancelled US tour
* Twelve Shots On The Rocks - (2002)
* Another Hostile Takeover - (2005)
* Street Poetry - (2007)
Notable Concerts
* December 31,1980 @ Virrat First known concert.
* August 26, 1983 @ Reading Festival Headliners were Black Sabbath and Thin Lizzy.
* December, 1983 @ The Marquee in London Where the video and live album All Those Wasted Years was filmed and recorded.
* April 23, 1984 @ Rock City, Nottingham Where the video The Nottingham Tapes was filmed, almost eight months before the death of the band’s drummer Razzle.
* December 4, 1984 @ Trax Club, Detroit The band’s final concert with drummer Razzle. Many dates had already been cancelled due to an injury of Monroe, however after Razzle’s death on December 8 the tour was cancelled indefinitely. 
* January 4, 1985 @ Kulttuuritalo, Helsinki Concert held in memorial of Razzle. Ex-Clash drummer Terry Chimes filled in on drums.
* May 19, 1985 @ Rockerina Festival, Poland Final concert before their split in May 1985. The concert was recorded and released as Rock &amp; Roll Divorce described as “the sound of a great band falling apart”. It featured René Berg on bass and Terry Chimes on drums.
* April 12, 2009 @ Tavastia Club, Helsinki Final show at the Tavastia. The video Buried Alive was filmed here. Featured members of Electric Boys playing alongside original Hanoi members Monroe and McCoy, with Nasty Suicide and Lacu as special guests.
* September 23, 2022 @ Helsinki Ice Hall Michael Monroe’s 60th Birthday Bash. The 2001-2004 lineup and 1980-1982 lineup both performed. With special guests Ginger, Karl Rockfist, Lenne-Kalle Taipale, Costello Hautamäki, Dave Lindholm, Dregen, Rich Jones and Steve Conte. Despite rumours, A.C. Christell and Conny Bloom did not appear. Demolition 23 served as the opening act. This is intended to be Hanoi Rocks’ final concert.
